    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "With the current implementation, it is not possible for us to provide such a feature. That being said, the combination of multiple sorts inside a single compare function is doable:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst compare = function(a, b) {\r\n  if (a.property1 < b.property1) return 1;\r\n  if (a.property1 > b.property1) return -1;\r\n  // property1 is equal for both\r\n  if (a.property2 < b.property2) return 1;\r\n  if (a.property2 > b.property2) return -1;\r\n  // property2 is equal for both\r\n  // ... and so on.\r\n\r\n  return 0;\r\n}\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2018-05-29T03:32:41Z",
